{ Distribution genealogy

  Debian based distributions:
    • Debian
    • LMDE (Linux Mint Debian Edition, Betsy)
    • Devuan

  Fedora based distributions:
    • Fedora
    • Korora
    • Chapeau

  Ubuntu based distributions:
    • Ubuntu
    • Zorin
    • elementary
    • Peppermint
    • Mint

  → Linux/distributions/arch[Arch] based distributions
    • Manjaro
    • Arch

  Red Hat based distributions
    • CentOS

  Suse based distributions:
    • openUSE


  Others:
    • Mageia
    • PCLinuxOS

}
{ Term distribution in Python

  The term *distribution* has a specfic meaning in Python packaging contexts where it refers to a source or binary distribution package of a single piece of Python language software.
 (In the sense of `→ development/languages/Python/libraries/setuptools[setuptools].dist.Distribution` or *sdist*).

}
